hardt|first=Adam|website=ComicBook.com|date=February 9, 2020|accessdate=February 10, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200210084509/https://comicbook.com/marvel/2020/02/09/morbius-set-photos-where-is-spider-man-sign/|archive-date=February 10, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"DisneyHaltsCoronavirus\">{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2020/03/disney-pausing-production-movies-little-mermaid-home-alone-nightmare-alley-coronavirus-1202882556/|title=Disney Pausing Production On Features \u2018Little Mermaid\u2019, \u2018Home Alone\u2019, \u2018Nightmare Alley\u2019 & More Until Coronavirus Calms Down|last=D'Alessandro|first=Anthony|work=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|date=March 13, 2020|accessdate=March 14, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200313191113/https://deadline.com/2020/03/disney-pausing-production-movies-little-mermaid-home-alone-nightmare-alley-coronavirus-1202882556/|archive-date=March 13, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"2021Date\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/sony-delays-release-morbius-ghostbusters-due-coronavirus-1285759|title=Sony Delays Release of 'Morbius,' 'Ghostbusters,' More Films Due to Coronavirus|last=Galuppo|first=Mia|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|date=March 30, 2020|access-date=March 30, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200331044545/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/sony-delays-release-morbius-ghostbusters-due-coronavirus-1285759|archive-date=March 31, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{Official website|https://www.morbius.movie/}}\n* {{IMDb title|7630550}}\n\n{{Sony's Marvel Universe}}\n{{Marvel Comics films}}\n{{Spider-Man films}}\n{{Daniel Espinosa}}\n\n[[Category:2020s action films]]\n[[Category:2020s superhero films]]\n[[Category:2021 horror films]]\n[[Category:American films]]\n[[Category:American action films]]\n[[Category:American horror films]]\n[[Category:American superhero films]]\n[[Category:Columbia Pictures films]]\n[[Category:English-language films]]\n[[Category:Films directed by Daniel Espinosa]]\n[[Category:Films postponed due to the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]]\n[[Category:Films produced by Avi Arad]]\n[[Category:Films produced by Lucas Foster]]\n[[Category:Films produced by Matt Tolmach]]\n[[Category:Films scored by Jon Ekstrand]]\n[[Category:Films shot in London]]\n[[Category:Films with screenplays by Matt Sazama and Burk Sharpless]]\n[[Category:Films with screenplays by Art Marcum and Matt Holloway]]\n[[Category:Sony's Marvel Universe films]]\n[[Category:Superhero horror films]]\n[[Category:Vampires in film]]\n", "name_user": "2605:e000:1300:ccbd:609c:d669:36ed:90bd", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Morbius_(film)"}
{"title_page": "Sylke von Gaza", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2018}}\n{{Infobox artist\n| name          = Sylke von Gaza\n| image         = Sylke von Gaza painting in Chiesa San Fantin Venezia 2014 (\u00a9 Bildarchiv Sylke von Gaza Foto Julian Bruno Vogel) 80.jpg\n| image_size    = \n| alt           = \n| caption       = Sylke von Gaza painting inside [[San Fantin, Venice|San Fantin]] church in [[Venice]], 2014\n| birth_name    = \n| birth_date    = {{Birth date and age|df=y|1966|07|01}} \n| birth_place   = [[Hamburg]], Germany\n| death_date    = <!-- {{Death date and age|df=y|YYYY|MM|DD|YYYY|MM|DD}} -->\n| death_place   = \n| nationality   = German\n| spouse        = \n| field         = Painting\n| training      = [[Academy of Fine Arts Munich]]\n| movement      = \n| works         = ''Red Veil Paintings'', ''Grey Veil Paintings''\n| patrons       = \n| awards        = [[Meistersch\u00fclerin]]<ref name=\":7\" /> (2007)\n| elected       = \n| website       = {{URL|vongaza.com/}}\n| bgcolour      = \n}}\n\n'''Sylke von Gaza''' (* 1 July 1966 in Hamburg as Sylke von Gazen genannt Gaza) is a German artist. First and foremost an [[Abstract art|abstract]] painter, she also pursues numerous projects that investigate the effect and impact of painting in architectural spaces and the process of painting including site-specific settings. Von Gaza lives and works in [[Munich]], Venice and [[Z\u00fcrich|Zurich]].\n\n== Life ==\nThe [[Hamburg]]-born artist Sylke von Gaza was first taken to Italy as a three-year-old by her great-grandmother, whom she accompanied on long journeys to Venice and the Emilia-Romagna. It was during those childhood visits to the churches of [[Ravenna]], [[Assisi]] and [[Venice]], to name but a few, that she first came to appreciate painting and architecture. The experience made a lasting impression and continues to inspire her work to this day.<ref name=\":10\">Giloy-Hirtz (2008): ''From the Grey to the Colourful.''</ref>\n\nSylke von Gaza's first university degree is in [[engineering|<u>engineering</u>]]. Later, as a student of painting at the [[Academy of Fine Arts, Munich|Academy of Fine Arts in Munich]] from 2002 to 2007 under the Irish painter [[Sean Scully]], she found herself drawn to the [[Old Master]]s and [[Abstract expressionism]].<ref name=\":4\">Giloy-Hirtz (2008): ''From the Grey to the Colourful'' & Drexler (2013): ''Sylke von Gaza in Conversation''.</ref> She completed her studies at the Academy of Fine Arts in Munich in 2007, graduating with a [[Meistersch\u00fcler]] diploma (\"summa cum laude\").<ref name=\":7\">[http://matrikel.adbk.de/ \"Matrikeldatenbank\"] (in German). Akademie der Bildenden K\u00fcnste M\u00fcnchen. Retrieved 2017-07-24. In the German academy tradition, \"Meistersch\u00fcler\" is the title awarded only to exceptionally talented students who successfully complete a postgraduate masterclass, equal to \"summa cum laude\".</ref>\n\n== Work ==\n[[Art of the Low Countries|Netherlandish]] and [[Italian Renaissance painting|Italian Renaissance]] painting has always been a key source of inspiration for Sylke von Gaza. With her large-scale abstract [[oil painting]]s she positions herself within the tradition of the Old Masters without, however, referencing them directly in her formal language.<ref name=\":4\" /> Oscillating between past and present, Venice provides an ideal creative environment for the artist,<ref name=\":5\" /> whose works not only probe the questions of tradition and [[Identity (social science)|identity]] in painting, but also provoke a discussion of the intrinsic value of art and society.<ref>Schmidt (2007): ''Die Schleier der Sylke von Gaza'' & Giloy-Hirtz (2008): ''From the Grey to the Colourful'' & Drexler (2013): ''Sylke von Gaza in Conversation'' & Sinninghe Damst\u00e9 (2013): ''Sacraments of a Deeper Reality''.</ref>\n\nHer work thus far can be divided into different strands. Her principal body of work consists of ''Early Works'', individual works, themed groups of works, site-specific works and the series of ''Veil Paintings'', among them the ''Grey Veil Paintings'' and ''Red Veil Paintings''.<ref name=\":4\" />\n\nIn Sylke von Gaza's creative practice, the [[veil]], the metaphor for [[Transcendence (philosophy)|transcendence]] and permeability, plays a central role.<ref name=\":2\">{{cite web|url=http://www.curator4art.de/sv-gaza.htm|title=Die Schleier der Sylke von Gaza \u2013 Who is afraid of grey, white and red?|last=Martin H. Schmidt|date=2007|language=German|accessdate=2017-07-25}}</ref><ref name=\":3\">Sinninghe Damst\u00e9 (2013): ''Sacraments of a Deeper Reality.''</ref> The ability to disclose by concealing, to render visible by shrouding \u2013 the artist has internalised this fundamental potential of painting and made it central to her work.<ref name=\":0\" />\n\nSince 2012, the artist has been working on projects that focus on painting in [[Sacred architecture|sacred spaces]],<ref name=\":3\" /> primarily in [[List of churches in Venice|Venetian churches]]. Since 2013, in collaboration with Curia Patriarchale di Venezia, von Gaza has been painting in the [[San Fantin, Venice|Chiesa San Fantin]] (2014), the [[San Lio, Venice|Chiesa San Lio]] (2015), the [[Santa Maria della Salute|Cappella Santissima Trinit\u00e0]] (2016).<ref name=\":1\">Ackermann (2015), ''Venedig wird abstrakt'', S. 111.</ref>\n\nTo mark the [[Venice Biennale]] of 2015, the Venetian Curia commissioned von Gaza with a site-specific work for the [[San Lio, Venice|Renaissance chapel of the Gussoni family]] in the church of [[San Lio, Venice|San Lio]]. Working on site inside the chapel during the ''Beyond the Veil'' project,<ref name=\":6\">{{cite web|url=http://www.veneziaupt.org/pls/veneziaupt/v3_s2ew_consultazione.mostra_pagina?id_pagina=633|title=Beyond the Veil: Red Veil Paintings nella Chiesa di San Lio|last=Gianmatteo Caputo|date=2015 |publisher=Uffici Beni Culturali & Turismo della Curia Patriarcale di Venezia UBC |language=it |accessdate=2017-07-18}}</ref> the artist created the ''Gussoni Red Veil Paintings Triptych'', which is now permanently installed in the Renaissance chapel designed around 1479 by [[Tullio Lombardo|Tullio]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://savevenice.org/our-restorations/church-of-san-lio-tullio-lombardo-pieta-with-saints/|title=Tullio Lombardo: Piet\u00e0 with Saints|date=2002|publisher=Save Venice Inc.|accessdate=2017-08-17}}</ref> and [[Pietro Lombardo]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://savevenice.org/our-restorations/church-of-san-lio-pietro-lombardo-gussoni-chapel/|title=Pietro Lombardo: Gussoni Chapel|date=2002|publisher=Save Venice Inc.|accessdate=2017-08-17}}</ref> The famous Venetian painter of [[Veduta]] Giovanni Antonio Canal (1697\u20131768), better known as [[Canaletto]], is buried in the chapel.<ref name=\":1\" />\n\nAt the invitation of the Seminario Patriarcale di Venezia von Gaza was creating the project ''Il Nido. A Pilgrimage towards Equilibrium''<ref name=\":11\" /> for the Padiglioni Paralleli<ref name=\":12\" /> in the [[Santa Maria della Salute|Basilica Santa Maria della Salute]] to coincide with the [[Venice Biennale|57th International Art Exhibition La Biennale di Venezia]] 2017.<ref>Ackermann (2017): ''[https://www.weltkunst.de/ausstellungen/2017/12/il-nido-venedigs-geheimes-nest Il Nido - Venedigs geheimes Nest]'' & Bernrieder (2017): ''Dem Blick entr\u00fcckte Huldigung'' & Jones (2017): ''\u201eAs High as the Eagle\u201c'' & Schaefer (2017): ''Hoch \u00fcber den Kirchend\u00e4chern von Venedig.''</ref>\n\n== Recognition ==\n* 2007: [[Meistersch\u00fcler]]in in Fine Arts at the [[Academy of Fine Arts, Munich|Akademie der Bildenden K\u00fcnste M\u00fcnchen]] under [[Sean Scully|Prof. Sean Scully]].<ref name=\":7\" />\n*2015: Work commission for Gussoni Renaissance Chapel by Curia Patriarcale di Venezia<ref name=\":6\" />\n*2017: Invitation to Padiglioni Paralleli for the for 57th Venice Biennale by Curia Patriarcale di Venezia<ref name=\":11\" />\n\n==  Exhibitions (selection) ==\n\n*2018: ''Gabriel & Lucifero. The most precious Pigment of Renaissance Venice'',<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.palazzocontarinipolignac.com/Content/pdf/Sylke_von_Gaza-Gabriel-Lucifero.pdf|title=Gabriel & Lucifero|date=2017-04-11|website=Palazzo Contarini Polignac}}</ref> [[Palazzo Contarini Polignac]], Venice (solo)\n*2018: ''BIAS Biennale Internazionale 2018'',<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.bias.institute/artisti-bias-2018/|title=Artisti BIAS 2018|website=BIAS Institute|language=Italian|access-date=2018-10-01}}</ref> [[Palazzo Riso|Museo Riso]], [[Capella dell'Icoronazione|Capella dell' Incoronazione]], Palermo\n*2018: ''Il Nido'' inside [[Santa Maria della Salute|Basilica Santa Maria della Salute]], Venice (solo)\n*2018: ''Il Nido'' at cloister of Seminario Patriarchale, Venice (solo)\n*2017: ''Il Nido. A Pilgrimage towards Equilibrium'',<ref name=\":11\">{{cite web|title=Sylke von Gaza: \"Il Nido. A Pilgrimage towards Equilibrium\" presso la Basilica della Salute, Padiglioni Paralleli 2017 |publisher=Curia Patriarcale di Venezia|url=http://www.veneziaupt.org/pls/veneziaupt/V3_S2EW_CONSULTAZIONE.mostra_pagina?id_pagina=658 |accessdate=2017-08-25 |last=Gianmatteo Caputo|date=2017 |language=it}}</ref> project start for Padiglioni Paralleli<ref name=\":12\">{{cite web|url=http://www.veneziaupt.org/pls/veneziaupt/V3_S2EW_CONSULTAZIONE.mostra_pagina?id_pagina=654&rifi=guest&rifp=guest|title=Padiglioni Paralleli alla Biennale 2017 |date=2017 |publisher=Curia Patriarcale di Venezia |language=it |accessdate=2017-07-22}}</ref> of Curia Patriarcale di Venezia and glasswork with [[Berengo Studio]],<ref>{{cite web|title=Berengo Studio|publisher=Berengo Studio 1988|url=https://www.berengo.com/|accessdate=2017-08-25|last=Adriano Berengo}}</ref> Murano, during [[Venice Biennale|57th Venice Biennale]], at [[Santa Maria della Salute|Basilica della Salute]], Osservatorio del Seminario Patriarcale, Punta della Dogana, [[Venice]] (solo)\n* 2017: ''Summertime: Br\u00fcning, Erben, von Gaza, Huidobro, Merschmann, M\u00fcnch'',<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.artnet.com/galleries/galerie-hans-strelow/summertime-br%C3%BCning-erben-von-gaza-huidobro/|title=Summertime: Br\u00fcning, Erben, von Gaza, Huidobro, Merschmann, M\u00fcnch|last=Hans Strelow|date=2017|publisher=Artnet|language=German|accessdate=2017-07-01}}</ref> [[Gallery Hans Strelow]], D\u00fcsseldorf\n* 2017: ''[[Art Cologne|52nd Art Cologne]]'', Gallery Hans Strelow, [[Cologne]]\n* 2016/17: ''Behind the Curtain. Concealment and Revelation since the Renaissance. From Titian to Cristo'',<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.smkp.de/en/curtain/|title=Exhibition 'Behind the Curtain. Concealment and Revelation since the Renaissance. From Titian to Christo'|publisher=Museum Kunstpalast|language=English|accessdate=2017-08-17}}</ref> curated by [[Beat Wismer]] and [[Prof. Dr. Claudia Bl\u00fcmle]], [[Museum Kunstpalast|Museum Kunstpalast D\u00fcsseldorf]]\n* 2016: ''Private View [[Liste der Kulturg\u00fcter in Z\u00fcrich/Kreis 8|Villa von Schulthess-Bodmer]]'', [[Z\u00fcrich]] (solo)\n* 2016: ''Fabrica Ecclesiae'',<ref>{{cite web|title=Fabrica Ecclesiae |publisher=Curia Patriarcale di Venezia|url=http://www.veneziaupt.org/pls/veneziaupt/v3_s2ew_consultazione.mostra_pagina?id_pagina=626 |accessdate=2017-08-17 |date=2016 |language=it}}</ref> Museo Diocesano d'Arte Sacra Sant' Apollonia, San Marco, Venice\n* 2015: ''Beyond the Veil'',<ref name=\":6\" /> project with and commission for Curia Patriarcale di Venezia during [[Venice Biennale|56th Venice Biennale]], [[San Lio, Venice|Chiesa San Lio]], Venice (solo)\n* 2014: ''Power of Glass'',<ref name=\":8\">''[https://www.hofglasmalerei.de/projekte/3144/power-of-glass-in-der-bayerischen-hofglasmalerei-2 Power of Glass.]'' Hofglasmalerei Gustav van Treeck, 2013, retrieved 2017-07-22 (in German). ([https://www.hofglasmalerei.de/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/gvt_pog_publication.pdf?x56254 PDF 1.2 MB Catalogue])</ref> [[Gustav 